Naming the Loop Variable
The loop variable can be named almost anything, but it should be meaningful.
These two examples do the same thing:
for fruit in fruits:
    print(fruit)
for x in fruits:
    print(x)
The first version is better because fruit tells the reader what kind of thing is being processed.






ImportantBest practice



Use a singular name for the loop variable and a plural name for the collection.
Examples:

for student in students:
for score in scores:
for city in cities:
for file in files:

Dictionary Looping Options
There are three common ways to loop over a dictionary.



Method
What you get




for key in dictionary:
Keys


for key in dictionary.keys():
Keys


for value in dictionary.values():
Values


for key, value in dictionary.items():
Key-value pairs




scores = {"Alice": 90, "Bob": 85, "Charlie": 92}

print("Keys:")
for name in scores:
    print(name)

print("\nValues:")
for score in scores.values():
    print(score)

print("\nKey-value pairs:")
for name, score in scores.items():
    print(name, score)


