Nested Data Example: Filtering Records
Suppose each dictionary represents one report. We can loop through the reports and print only those with a high priority level.

reports = [
    {"id": 1, "topic": "cyber", "priority": "high"},
    {"id": 2, "topic": "trade", "priority": "medium"},
    {"id": 3, "topic": "conflict", "priority": "high"}
]

for report in reports:
    if report["priority"] == "high":
        print(f"Report {report['id']}: {report['topic']}")


